single_game_results.explain: You place any object that is NOT a pillow on the bed and you get points for each non-pillow item on the bed when the game ends.
single_game_results.overall: Overly simplistic, geared more toward a toddler and not at all engaging.   Just a repetitive action over and over.  No challenge, very uninteresting.

single_game_results.explain: You put a hex bin near a rug and throw objects in a doggie bed or in the bin.   You get points for landing in the doggie bed, the bin or just because you threw it and it eventually stopped moving.
single_game_results.overall: This isn't a game, it's just throwing stuff.  You get a point for everything you throw since everything will eventually stop moving, so there's not even motivation to throw the ball INTO the bin or doggie bed.   Pointless.

debrief_responses.comments: No, but that was an interesting exercise, thank you!  I hope I didn't sound too much like a broken record.  :)
debrief_responses.strategy: I considered the clarity of the game, the rules and the scoring system and overall did they seem enjoyable (spoiler: No.) I also looked at the difficulty level - like were they too easy like just getting a point every time you threw something or too hard like trying to get a ball to land on TOP of an open bin.  Also was the logic of the scoring system was off base and would that lead to you having no motivation to play.   I also considered motivation, which I found lacking in all of them, either because the tasks were too simple or the scoring was out of whack.

single_game_results.explain: In this game you will be stacking blocks one upon another, kind of like building a tower. the blocks must be stacked in the proper order. Start with a bridge block first. Place a flat block on the bridge block, then a tall cylindrical block on the flat block, then a cube on top of the cylinder & top it all off with a pyramid block. You get 10 points for each set of blocks you succesfully stack in this order.
single_game_results.overall: this seems like a fun way to learn to manipulate objects in a virtual environment. I think I would enjoy trying this game out & I would definitely need things like this to help me learn how to properly utilize a new virtual space.

single_game_results.explain: Throw dodgeballs around the room but be careful not to let them land in a doggie bed. You'll get 1 point for every ball thrown but you lose 3 points if a ball lands in a doggie bed.
single_game_results.overall: This one could be a bit tricky. You have to learn how trajectories work in this environment fairly quickly and then apply it immediately considering the scoring rules.

This could be really difficult. I'm not sure I could pull this off. In real life it would be extremely difficult. Not sure how it would work in a virtual environment but it is a good way to learn the physics of said environment.
single_game_results.explain: Place a hexagonal bin near the rug & make sure it stays there for the duration of the game.  Now, throw a dodgeball in such a way that it lands on top of the hexagonal bin & stays there. You get one point every time you successfully land a ball on top of the bin & it stays.

Using a tall rectangular block as a base, stack 2 more tall rectangular block & a third block of your choice on top of it. Order doesn't seem to matter just as long as they stay stacked on top of the initial tall rectangular block. Your score will be 1.4 time the number of successful stacks you have at the end of the game.
single_game_results.overall: This is another excellent game for learning to manipulate objects in a virtual space & for learning  the physics of it.

single_game_results.explain: Throw a dodgeball. You get 1 point for each throw once the ball comes to a stop.

single_game_results.overall: I think it would make for a fun time killer. This would probably make for a good "on the go" phone game.
single_game_results.explain: You basically pick up blocks off of a rug and toss them. Your scoring will depend on the number of different blocks that are thrown by the time the game is terminated.

First find the rug. Next, place the garbage can shaped like a hexagon near the rug. Make sure the can remains there throughout game play. You will next grab some dodgeballs. Your objective is to land the balls either in or on top of the hexagonal bin, on top of the desk or on the bed. You earn a point for landing the ball on any of these objects. Your final score is determined by the number of balls landed.
single_game_results.overall: I think it would be challenging. I could see myself having fun playing this many times in succession.

single_game_results.explain: Stand next to the desk, and move a variety of things on or off the bed. 5 points are gained for placing said objects on either the doggie bed, the chair or the laptop. 1 point is earned from objects that land on the bed and stay, but aren't the 3 previously mentioned objects. 5 points are deducted for objects that don't stay on the bed.
single_game_results.overall: I think this would be a good skill game, to test eye/hand coordination.

single_game_results.explain: Throw balls into the garbage bin, and then place CDs, pencils and credit cards into the bin or the top desk drawer. Score depends on the number CDs and credit cards in the bin. Points deducted are 3 times the amount of balls in the garbage bin, the number of CDs, credit cards and pencils in the top drawer, and how many CDs and cards didn't make it into the bin.
single_game_results.overall: I think this would be rather tedious. Keeping track of what to put where would get old fast, I would think.

single_game_results.explain: Move objects onto the rug, including dodgeballs. Throw the balls so they land on top of the garbage bin. 1 point is earned for each ball that makes it on top of the bin. 70 points may be earned for the number of objects that are still near the rug, which is multiplied by the number of ball remaining on the rug.
single_game_results.overall: This game would be fun to play sporadically, say on a rainy day or lunch break. It doesn't involve too much deep stratagy.
This game seems kinda boring. There's no real challenge to it. Also, repetitive, in a non challenging way.
single_game_results.explain: Pick up the cubes. Throw them or gently set them down. Pick them up again and place them down again. Try to do this without any movement. 1 point for every block you throw, and 15 for putting it down, lifting it again and placing it down with no movement.

Place the bin next to the door, and make sure it stays there for the duration of the game. Move objects so they are still and near the rug. Throw the balls so that they are still when they land or land on top of the bin and stay still
single_game_results.overall: The instructions are really hard to follow. I'm sure it would be fun, but has a learning curve to some degree.
The instructions don't seem to make a whole lot of sense. I can sense it would take a while to get the hang of this game.
single_game_results.explain: Place the bin in close proximity to the top shelf. It will stay there for the duration of the game. Pick up, hold and release green triangles, throw dodgeballs onto the bin and throw the cube blocks in general. Score depends on how many times the green triangles have been  picked up, dropped and picked up again. Also, the number of times you've thrown the cube blocks, as well as thrown one in motion. Finally, the number of times you've thrown a ball onto the bin and stays counts for the same point amount.

Pick up the cubes and place them inside the buildings, and either remove them or leave them. Game terminates when you've handled any cube 3 or so times. points are dependent on how many times put a cube in a building and it was removed or the gam ends.
single_game_results.overall: The game sems simple enough. I can see myself growing bored with it rather quickly however.

single_game_results.explain: Put a chair in the center of the room. It can't face the desk or the bed. It must stay there for the entirety of the game. Stand next to the bed and throw dodgeballs onto the bed on to the chair, into the bin or other locations in the room. 5 points for each ball that lands in the bin, and 1 each for the bed and the chair. 1 point is subtracted for it landing elsewhere in the room. You then add up your points to determine your score. The game terminates after you earn 10 or more points.
single_game_results.overall: This game sounds like it would be quite involved, but in a good way. It would keep me occupied for quite a while.

single_game_results.explain: The goal of this game is to get chairs on the desk and in motion. The goal is to score thirty points, which requires a lot of chairs on the desk and in motion at the end of the game.

single_game_results.overall: This seems like a reasonably fun game given the constraints of the room and would be a good way to pass time.
single_game_results.explain: This is a shooting game where different kinds of balls score different points, and how close you get to the goal you are also effects points. If you use diffferent balls, and get closer you score more, while you you use a larger ball and land further away you score less..

single_game_results.overall: This feels like a think I would do when I was a kid when I was trying to pass the time. A little meaningless game to pass the time that doesn't really matter to anyone but the player.
single_game_results.explain: Try to get as many doge-balls to land and stop on the top shelf in 30 seconds after player throws them on to the shelf.

A homemade version of skeeball where the curve ramp is used for the base and the hexagon bin is used in place of the main part of a skeeball game. The goal of this game is to roll balls up the ramp into the bin. However given the size of the bin this feels too easy.
single_game_results.overall: I think it is too easy. The difficulty in skeeball is the number of holes you have to shoot into, the size of the hexagon bin means that with enough force you will score everytime and this will limit the fun of this game.

I don't see how there is any logic to this game. There is no way to score, or win. the score always stays the same as the scores cancels out. I don't understand this as a game or why this would be fun.
single_game_results.explain: You place credit cards or CDs into the hexagonal bin. However, this does not change the score because the score cancels out so I don't understand what the win condition could be for this game or how it could ever end or progress.

single_game_results.overall: There is not constraint on this game, other than pillows. How long does it last? What makes it hard? There is no obstacle to overcame that makes this a game worth playing.
single_game_results.explain: Place non-pillow objects on the bed until the end of the game, and score one point for every non-pillow object on the bed at the end of the game.

single_game_results.overall: It is simple, but it makes sense. It would be more fun with a second player to play defense and/or a time constraint this would add levels to make the game more of a sport, but as it stands this is the kind of thing a person would do to pass time in this room.
single_game_results.explain: A simple shooting game where you try to shoot the dodgeball into the hexagonal bin. Scoring one point each time you successfully shoot the ball into this goal.

You throw the ball against the wall and then try to catch it or touch it after it touches the wall. You score a point for throwing the ball. A point for it hitting the wall, and a third point for getting the ball after it returns
single_game_results.overall: This is like something I would do when I was a kid. I would change the rules so you score more for grabbing the ball on return than just touching it because those shouldn't be worth the same amount.

single_game_results.explain: The blue cube clock is placed on the rug and then other objects are moved around the room. You score points based on objects that have not moved and are near the north wall or yellow and blue blocks are sandiwhced.
single_game_results.overall: I don't understand this game at all. Things are moving is ways that I can't conceptualize. I don't understand the scoring. I don't really get the game play. None of it makes sense to me.

debrief_responses.strategy: I thought about the games I have played, or the kinds of games I have seen other people, children mostly, create when they are bored. I think about he way they create play and task to kill their time and how that fits with a logic. I also thought about how that then can be worked out to a fuller game with a logical rule set, as we have in sports. To think about if these games made sense.
debrief_responses.aids: I looked up the name of cornhole on google because I couldn't think of the name of it off the top of my head. Other than that I wrote everything myself.
debrief_responses.comments: A little repetitive, but pays well

single_game_results.overall: I like this game. It's a little bizarre, but in a good way. With a little imagination, this game can be very enjoyable.
single_game_results.explain: You throw dodgeballs and try to land them in the hexagonal bin. You can also place CDs and credit cards in the bin. You get a point for each dodgeball you throw and 40 points for every dodgeball that lands in the bin multiplied by the number of CDs and credit cards in the bin.

You must stack matching blocks. After putting a bin near a wall, you can throw golf balls on or in it. Your final score is the amount of blocks you stacked but minus the number of golf balls you have on or in the bin multiplied by four.
single_game_results.overall: It doesn't make sense. The rules make it so that the player shouldn't aim to throw the golf balls in or on the bin at all.
It's a basic hide-and-seek, but with cellphones. I can imagine a lot of players enjoying playing this.
single_game_results.explain: After putting the bin next to the rug, find CDs and cellphones and put them inside the bin for 2 points each.
Put the bin near the rug, then throw dodgeballs to have as many as you can end up either on the desk or in the bin. Your score is every ball that remains on either of those 2 places.
single_game_results.overall: It would be fun and challenging. Not only do you have to land the ball in those places, but you need to make sure the previous balls don't get knocked off from the new ones you throw.
It's nice and simple. This is a game many already are familiar with.
single_game_results.explain: You stand on the rug and throw 10 balls, trying to get them in the bin. Your score is however many balls end up inside the bin.
Clear out the top drawer and put as many items in it as possible. You get a point for each item you fit in there.
single_game_results.overall: This one is the best so far. I can imagine player jamming things in there that maybe wouldn't fit, haha!

single_game_results.explain: You throw dodgeballs without landing them on the doggie bed. At the end of the game, you get a point for every ball that is still but lose 3 points for every ball that's on the doggie bed.
single_game_results.overall: This is a fun game with a little challenge with it. You can throw the balls as hard as you want. If one ends up on the dog's bed, you must throw another ball to knock it off of there.

single_game_results.explain: Put a green golf ball and a dodgeball near the door and stand by them. Make sure the golf ball don't move for the whole game. Then throw dodgeballs or other objects aiming for the bin. The game ends when you finish throwing 3 things or when you throw a dodgeball for the second time and it stops moving. You get 10 points for each thing you throw in the bin.
single_game_results.overall: This game seems rather short or that you need to keep too careful an eye on what you're doing. I think it will be easy for player to break the rules of this game.

single_game_results.explain: You get a point for each block you throw. Your score is however many blocks you threw by the end of the game.
single_game_results.overall: It is very, very simple but it sounds like some quick fun. Not much else to say. The rules are rather simple.

This game is rather complex.  There is really no incentive for the player to throw the ball inside the bin. Placing the CDs and cards are also a losing situation. At any point, a card or CD will not be in the top drawer (because it's in the bin) or not in the bin (because it's in the top drawer).
single_game_results.explain: Find credit cards, CDs, and pencils to either put inside the top drawer or inside the bin. You can also throw balls inside the bin. Your score at the end of the game is however many cards and CDs inside the bin MINUS the number of balls not in the bin, the number of credit cards and CDs that's not inside the bin or top drawer, and the pencils that aren't in the top drawer all multiplied by three.

single_game_results.explain: First place a hexagonal bin near a door and leave there for the entire game.  Then throw dodge balls until it either lands in the bin or anywhere outside when the ball stops.
single_game_results.overall: Sounds simple but confusing at the same because of how the gameplay is described. I am not sure how I would be able to play this until I physically interacted with the game.

single_game_results.explain: First I place a hexagonal bin near a rug and keep it there for entire game. Then to score points I must either place chair on top of desk or make a basketball land on top of the bin. I make more points if it lands on the bin.
single_game_results.overall: It seems like fun game that would keep me entertain for awhile. I can also setup a competition to play with friends.
Its a fun and simple game that I can play alone. Another good thing is that not a lot of things are needed to play.
single_game_results.explain: The gameplay lasts 30 seconds and I must throw dodgeballs until they land and stop on top of the shelf. I receive 1 point for each dodgeball that stops on the shelf.
The game play is moving any objects near a rog and door and also breaking the objects. I gain points by either placing objects near the rug or door and broken objects.
single_game_results.overall: Seems like it can be boring as time passes because there is no challenge in playing the game. Maybe if it was versus someone, then it might become more interesting.

single_game_results.explain: The goal is to pick up the teddy bear from the chair and throw it. You get 5 points if the teddy bear lands in the bin and 1 point if it touches a ball. Place the ramp in the middle, the chair in front of it, and the ball near the bin.
single_game_results.overall: Seems like it can be a fun with friends. This can be challenging and entertaining.
It can be a little confusing because of how the game play is described.
single_game_results.explain: I pick up chairs and release them to make them move. You score 1 point each time a chair stops moving after you let it go. The game ends when your total score reaches 10 or more. You earn 4 points for each chair that ends up on a desk and is still moving at the end of the game.
Try to land the dodgeballs on either a dog bed or the hexagonal bin near a rug. You score points for each successful throw, and your final score is the total of these points.
single_game_results.overall: Sounds like it can a fun game to play by myself. Also not a lot things are needed to play.

single_game_results.explain: It's a game where you throw a ball, make it touch a wall, and then either catch it or touch it again. You earn 1 point for each successful throw, where the ball hits the wall, and you either catch it or touch it after its flight.
single_game_results.overall: It sounds very repetitive but sounds like it can very fun because I would be focus on not dropping the ball.
Sounds like it can be fun but a little complicated. The scoring system is not that great.
single_game_results.explain: You start with red pyramid blocks on a rug. The game involves picking up and throwing cube blocks, placing yellow cubes in buildings, and stacking blocks with a yellow cube on top of a matching block.

You start with an empty shelf and need to create a building with exactly six objects. Hold blocks without placing them, interact by moving them, and throw a block that was inside a building if you touch it while holding another. At the end, make sure blocks are stacked based on certain rules. Score points for unique objects held, bonus for specific building conditions, and lose points for throwing blocks from non-setup buildings.
single_game_results.overall: Seems like it can be a little complicated on how the gameplay is described. The scoring is also not great.

debrief_responses.strategy: I thought about how I would feel actually playing each game.  I thought about how challenging or fun they would be.  I like games with a good challenge.

single_game_results.overall: This game seems pretty simple.  However, it could be more difficult than it sounds if it is hard to move the ball or pick it up and throw it.
single_game_results.explain: To set up the game, I will place a dodgeball near the desk.  To play the game, I need to pick up a dodgeball and throw it.  I will get one point every time I throw a dodgeball and it comes to a stop.

single_game_results.overall: The game seems boring.  It could be challenging, though, if the blocks are difficult to manipulate.
single_game_results.explain: I need to pick up some blocks and place them inside of a building of some sort.  Then I can take them out of the building or leave them there.  The game will end when I have picked up and put down the same block a minimum of three times.    The score is determined by how many times I have placed a block in the building.

single_game_results.overall: This game seems pointless, unless the point is to learn how to move and manipulate things in VR.  I think it would be boring.
single_game_results.explain: I need to find and pick up credit cards or CDs and place them in the hexagonal bin that is on the floor.  I will not score any points.  My score will remain zero.

I need to move chairs, put them on the desk and set them in motion.  I will get one point for every chair that is on a desk and in motion at the end of the game.  The game will not end until I get a score of 30 or more.
single_game_results.overall: I think this game would be challenging.  I would have to figure out how to put the chairs on the desk and set them in motion.  I would have to figure out how to get to 30 points when there are only two chairs and one desk.
This game could be fun if I could definitely figure out how to do it.  I'm not sure, though.
single_game_results.explain: I have to play with blocks by repeatedly picking them up, throwing them and putting them down.  I would get 15 points every time I picked up a block, set it down, picked it up again and set it down again without movement.  I would only get one point for throwing a block.
I need to pick up objects in the room and put them on the bed.  I will get one point for every object on the bed that is not a pillow.
single_game_results.overall: I like this game.  It would be fun gathering up stuff from the room and putting it on the bed.  I would need to figure out if I should take the pillows off the bed.
I like this game.  It seems fun and challenging.
single_game_results.explain: I need to pick up the hexagonal bin and put it near the rug.  Then I need to get a dodgeball, hold it and throw it in the bin.  I will get one point every time I get a dodgeball in the bin.

I need to more object so that they are near the rug and the door.  I also need to break some objects.  The score depends on the number or objects I get near the door or near the rug and the number of broken objects.
single_game_results.overall: This game could be very fun.  I would have to figure out how to break objects, though.  That could be a challenge.

single_game_results.explain: I need to place the wooden ramp in front of the hexagonal bin.  I will throw a dodgeball do that it rolls up the ramp and go into the bin.  I get a point for every ball I get into the bin.
single_game_results.overall: This is a great game.  It would be a lot of fun.  I would love the challenge.
This seems really boring.  I would not like to play this game.
single_game_results.explain: I need to either pick up blocks, set them down and pick them up again without moving them (3 points) or pick up a block and throw it (1 point).

debrief_responses.comments: I hope i can be invited to more of these. This was very enjoyable study and i had a blast completing it! Thank you so much for the opportunity!

single_game_results.explain: This game to me is  sort of like basketball. You place the dodgeballs on the desk and use the bin as sort of a basket  and throw the balls into the bin.
single_game_results.overall: My overall impression of this game is it is a unique spin on basketball within these rooms. I also like that you have to line up the balls and place the bin to be able to throw balls into it. Sounds fun!
Overall it sounds like a very challenging game that will require some skill and some smarts to be able to do properly but it sounds confusing also.
single_game_results.explain: This sounds like taking the chairs and placing them on the desk and making sure they are rolling or moving.

single_game_results.overall: Sounds like a straight forward game that is easy to follow instructions on and have fun with. Not a lot of prep to play this one so you can get right into the action.
single_game_results.explain: Simply stand on the rug and throw the balls into the hexagonal bin and after 10 throws the game ends with your  score being the balls inside the bin that aren't moving.

single_game_results.overall: This game sounds like a fresh idea and sounds challenging. Definitely comes off to me as innovative and exciting from the sound of it.
single_game_results.explain: Place a hex bin near the door and make sure it doesn't move and place credit cards or cds into the hex bin and throw white golfballs in the bin and make sure they stop to get 1 point and get 40 points for each cd and card in the bin.
Put any objects that are not pillows on the bed and get 1 point for each item.
single_game_results.overall: This is a very easy game to understand and to complete. Just remove the pillows and put everything on the bed that is not a pillow. Though the challenge may be trying to fit everything on the bed without it falling off.

single_game_results.explain: Put a hex bin on the east wall and make sure it does not move for the entire game and throw dodgeballs with the intent of them stopping in the bin.
single_game_results.overall: This game is somewhat challenging but not overly so. It strikes me as a lightly challenging fun entertaining game that requires tossing dodgeballs with some strategy.
This one sounds interesting and challenging. The scoring system is quite confusing for this game though and very difficult to understand. This doesn't sound like my kind of game.
single_game_results.explain: We need the hexagonal bin for this game and we are to put credit cards, cds, and pencils either into the top drawer or the bin. Placing these items in the bin help towards our score.

single_game_results.overall: Sounds like a fun game that requires some strategy and planning before your throws to avoid the doggie beds. Fun game with a nice balance to be challenging but enjoyable.
single_game_results.explain: Throw dodgeballs around he room but make sure they dont land in the doggie bed or you lose 3 points compared to the 1 gained for balls that do not land inside the bed.

single_game_results.overall: Very fun and very challenging. Having to land the dodgeballs on these spots and making sure they stop moving will be a challenge. Sounds like an addictive game.
single_game_results.explain: Throwing dodgeballs and trying to get them to land on a side table, bed or on TOP of the hex bin. Receiving 1 point for each ball that lands in these spots and stops moving.

single_game_results.overall: Very fun and sounds like it will be very popular if people play it. I would enjoy this game a lot and i think it would be one of my favorites as it has challenging aspects as well as fun tied to it.
single_game_results.explain: Put a hex bin near the rug and make sure it doesnt move for the entirety of the game. then place chairs on desk and throw basketballs so they land on top of the hex bin. 1 point for every chair on the desk and 40 points for every ball you get to stop on top of the hex bin. Basically like a coin flip game where you flip a coin to get it to stay on a plate but with a twist. very interesting

The goal of the game is to throw golfballs and dodgeballs aimed to land on top of a hexagonal bin. You earn 1 point for each golfball that stops on top of the bin, 1 point for each dodgeball that stops inside, and 1 point for each dodgeball that stops on top of the bin.
single_game_results.overall: There are good objectives and it is a bit challenging. Still it is not that interesting.

single_game_results.explain: The goal of the game is to throw golfballs on a hexagonal bin and then to throw basketballs or white golfballs onto the top drawer or onto a hexagonal bin. You earn 1 point for each golfball that rests on a hexagonal bin. You score is multiplied 40 times the number of successful throws for each type of throw.
single_game_results.overall: This game has an objective and seems a bit more difficult than the previous two games.

single_game_results.explain: The goal of the game is to move chairs so that they end up on desks and are in motion. Once your score is 30 or more, the game ends. One point is earned for each chair that is on a desk and in motion at the end of the game.
single_game_results.overall: It seems a little confusing. But after viewing it might make more sense.

single_game_results.explain: The goal of the game is to throw a ball so it touches a wall and then either catch it or touch it. You earn one point for each time you successfully throw the ball, it touches a wall, and and you are holding it again or touching it after its flight.
single_game_results.overall: The game seem fairly easy to understand but it it not that interesting.

single_game_results.explain: First place a hexagonal bin near a triangular ramp and make sure it stays put till the end of the game. The goal is to hold a ball and throw it so that it touches a triangular ramp and then lands inside the hexagonal bin. If the hexagonal bin is no longer upright without being touched or held, the game ends. 1 Point is earned after each successfully thrown ball that touches the ramp and lands in the bin.
single_game_results.overall: The game has an objective and seems interesting to play. This is the game I would like to play the most so far.
The game has an objective. It seems a little more difficult than previous games. It seems a little interesting.
single_game_results.explain: The goal of the game is to throw dodgeballs so they land on a doggie bed or a hexagonal bin, or to stop moving after being thrown. You earn 1 point for each dodgeball that lands on a doggie bed, 1 point for each dodgeball that lands on a hexagonal bin, and 1 point for each dodgeball that stops moving after being thrown.
The goal of the game is to hold and throw a dodgeball. You get 1 point for each time you throw a dodgeball and it comes to a stop.
single_game_results.overall: The game has a boring objective. This would not keep my attention for being long.

single_game_results.explain: First put a hexagonal bin near a rug and keep it there for the rest of the game. The goal of the game is to throw dodgeballs and aim the to land inside the hexagonal bin or on a doggie bed. You earn points for each dodgeball that is able come to a rest inside the hexagonal bin or doggie bed. Your final score will be the sum of the successful throws.
single_game_results.overall: The game is a little interesting. I do think it would get pretty repetitive in a short amount of time.

single_game_results.explain: The goal of the game is to place objects that are not pillows on the bed. 1 point is earned for each item that is not a pillow placed on the bed at the end of the game.
single_game_results.overall: The game is boring and too simple. There seems to be really no challenge presented here.
The game is easy. It seems rather boring.
single_game_results.explain: The goal of the game is to throw dodgeballs so that they land and come to rest on the top shelf. The game will then end after 30 seconds. You earn 1 point for each dodgeball that is resting on the top shelf at the end of the game.

debrief_responses.strategy: I considered how fun it seemed like it would be. I tried to imagine playing it and then tried to imagine if it's something I'd even have an interest in doing in a virtual environment.
debrief_responses.comments: Whatever AI is coming up with these 'games' has to be some low end model like 7B at most. They're like feverdreams of random crap thrown together that barely function as a game. A child would most likely think they're boring let alone an adult.
debrief_responses.aids: I copy/pasted the instructions onto notepad so I could refer to them.

single_game_results.overall: Seems like it could be fun for a short tutorial. I can't see myself doing it more than once ever though and then never touching the 'game' again. Very basic, like throwing paper balls in a bin.
single_game_results.explain: Throw balls at a ramp and try to get them to land in a bin. If the bin falls over it's game over. One point for each ball in the bin that touched the ramp first.
Throw a pink ball so that it hits a ramp and then lands on the bed or comes to a stop while touching me. Score is Times the dodgeball landed on bed-number of times it touched me and stopped.
single_game_results.overall: It seems very boring and pointless. I would have no interest in playing this game at all.

single_game_results.explain: Place a bin next to the bed, throw balls at the bin. Points vary based on the ball that goes in the bin and you lose 1 point for each miss.
single_game_results.overall: Again its just throwing balls in a bin. The scoring system makes no sense it would be impossible to lose. Seems boring and half baked as a game idea.

single_game_results.explain: Roll golf balls on a rug and get a point when they stop?
single_game_results.overall: The game makes no sense at all. Roll balls on a rug and get a point when they stop? Objects on the rug give a point too? What? I don't get it.

single_game_results.explain: Place blue blocks on the rug and keep them there. Move the rest of the objects in the room near the north wall and extra points for color combinations?
single_game_results.overall: This again seems like a pointless game. I'm not even sure I entirely understand it at all. What does putting the blue blocks on the rug have to do with anything? Why am I moving things to the north wall?

single_game_results.explain: Throw balls and try to get them to land in a bin or on a doggie bed. Points for either.
single_game_results.overall: Just a standard ball throwing game. Try to get them in a bin or on the dog bed. Not too difficult, would probably get boring incredibly quickly.
I'm not sure how you throw a bouncing ball on a rug and have it roll. Eitherway the game doesn't seem very fun and incredibly basic.
single_game_results.explain: Roll balls on the rug and try to get them to rest on a bin. Points for each ball thrown and extra points if they stop on the bin.

single_game_results.overall: I mean it's still just throwing balls into a bin. Only difference here is it's two different balls, you're still playing the same boring game of putting balls inside something though. Would play it once and move on.
single_game_results.explain: Throw basketballs and dodgeball into a bin. 1 Point for a dodgeball .1 for a basketball.

single_game_results.overall: Not sure I understand it entirely. How would I land balls both on and in the bin? A bin normally doesn't have a surface you can land something on if you're still putting things in it. Still, it's a confusing and sounds like equally boring game.
single_game_results.explain: Throw golfballs and dodgeballs and try to get them to land on top of a bin. Points for each one that lands on top or inside the bin??
Put chairs on the desk and throw golfballs onto the desk. Throw dodgeball into bins and stack cube blocks on top of each other. Points for...doing each of those I guess.
single_game_results.overall: This game just makes no sense at all. Why are the chairs on the desk? You get points for just doing things and have no way to lose points. This barely qualifies as a game and more like a checklist of things to do.

single_game_results.overall: This game seems easy enough to play, not sure how fun it would be
single_game_results.explain: Pick up and place cubed blocks into buildings, you need to put down at least 3
Seems like a digital version of corn hole, place a bin by the door and try to throw dodgeballs as close to the bin or on top of it.
single_game_results.overall: This one seems like it would be more fun to play than the last one.
Not really sure what the point of this game would be, but would give it a go.
single_game_results.explain: Put a doggie bed near the rug, move objects onto the bed without having them move afterwards.
This seems like a digital version of skeeball, roll a ball up the ramp and have it land on the bed, you lose point if it rolls back to you.
single_game_results.overall: This would be fun to try, I think I have a good idea of how to play it.

single_game_results.explain: Place a bin near the drawer and throw credit cards, CDs, and pencil into the bin.  YOu lose points if anything lands in the drawer
single_game_results.overall: This game doesn't make a lot of sense, not really sure I have a grasp of the rules.

single_game_results.explain: Put a bin next to the rug, score points by putting cellphones or CDs into the bin.
single_game_results.overall: Not really sure if this is a throw/aim game or a hide and seek game (you have to find the objects)

single_game_results.explain: Throw or place blocks without having them move
single_game_results.overall: Not really sure what the point of this game is, it would seem that you should get more points for throwing a cube without having it move.

single_game_results.explain: Throw a dodgeball and have it come to a stop
single_game_results.overall: Not really sure what the point of this game is, it sound like just throwing a ball and waiting for it to come to a stop

single_game_results.explain: Place various objects in the top drawer but make sure at some point the drawer is empty.  You get more point for different objects.
single_game_results.overall: I guess you just start off emptying the drawer then fill it as much as possible to score more points.

single_game_results.explain: Throw dodgeballs at the bed, bin, or sidetable.  You get points if it lands and stop moving.
single_game_results.overall: This would be one of the more fun games to play, I think it would be challenging.

single_game_results.explain: Dodge Basketball - stand near the door and try to toss dodgeballs into the hex basket. Each basket gives 10 points.
single_game_results.overall: Would be good for people who like to play basketball. Could be boring to those who see it as simply "throwing trash away."

single_game_results.explain: Throw balls into a hex bin for 10 or 20 points.
single_game_results.overall: I like the ball size variation in this version. However, simply  throwing from a stationary position isn't very challenging.
I like experiencing all the areas in the room, but the lack of scoring details confuses me. Also, are both actions completed at the same time? Or randomly, one at a time?
single_game_results.explain: Move different objects to assigned locations, while holding and throwing dodgeballs on top of a hex bin. Scoring is unclear.
Move objects into a centrally-located, stationary hex bin. Objects can be picked up, or set in motion.
single_game_results.overall: I'd like to set everything in motion and see what chaos happens. This has the potential to be a really fun, unpredictable game.
Compared to the other versions, this one lacks motion and excitement. It could use some type of variation.
single_game_results.explain: Hold, then throw a dodgeball so it lands on a stationary hex bin. Successful lands earn 1 point.
Throw balls into a stationary hex bin located near the north wall. Dodgeballs earn 1 point and basketballs earn 0.1 point.
single_game_results.overall: I imagine I'd get bored with this one after a few minutes, once I learned the exact movements I needed. This one also needs some variation beyond two types of balls.

single_game_results.explain: Adjust or move objects so they are near a rug and stationary when the game ends- after three minutes have passed. Each stationary, near-the-rug object earns 1 point.
single_game_results.overall: I like the imagination of this game. Specifically, the objects in motion and endless variations of play.
There isn't much strategy or skill involved in this one. I don't think I'd enjoy it, but a young child might.
single_game_results.explain: Earn 1 point for each cube thrown onto the rug. Earn 3 points for each cube that is picked up, then set down, then picked up again without moving its position/location.
Throw dodgeballs into a stationary hex bin hear the rug, or on top of the desk. Scoring is unclear but accomplishing either one/both earns points.
single_game_results.overall: It would be challenging to get the ball to land on top of the desk, but easy to throw it into the bin. Slightly challenging, but not enough to keep my interest.
This could be interesting game play. If objects must wind up stationary, this means many are moveable. Has the potential for unforeseen events.
single_game_results.explain: Move objects onto a doggie bet near the rug, ensuring the objects are stationary at the end of the game. Earn 1 point for each stationary object on the doggie bed when the game ends.

single_game_results.explain: There is a bin near the room center which you have to pick up and place objects into the bin, or set them in motion by rolling or tossing them into the bin. Each object into the bin earns a single point.
single_game_results.overall: Dull, boring, computer generated without any sense of human entertainment taken into consideration. Not very fun at all.

single_game_results.explain: Throw dodgeballs into the hex bin, once each ball lands in the bin and stops moving in the bin you get one point.
single_game_results.overall: Boring. This is not a game, sort of a time passer people do when bored. It seems AI generated, without human touch.

single_game_results.explain: Place a bin near the rug. Put chairs on the desks and throw basketballs so they land on TOP of the bin, not in it. You get 1 point for each chair placed on a desk and 40 for every basketball that stops moving on top of the bin.
single_game_results.overall: Near impossible. The probabilities of throwing a basketball and having it land on top of an open bin and stay is crazy. The chairs on desks? This game makes no sense, it is nonsense AI. Definitely not human.

single_game_results.explain: Place a curved wood ramp next to the rug make sure it stays in place. Hold a beachball, throw it so it rolls on the curved wooden ramp and make sure it rolls down stopping on the rug. Points based on the rug color where the ball stops. 1 for pink 2 for yellow 3 for orange 3 for green 4 for purple.
single_game_results.overall: The ramp being next to the rug is a problem. THe ball will want to roll backdown the ramp, avoiding the rug. This game is near impossible to play, AI generated and not human at all. Very boring, very difficult if at all possible.

single_game_results.explain: Place a bin near the rug. Make sure it stays there. Hold and throw a dodgeball so it touches the top shelf and then lands and rests on the bin. 1 point is earned for each successful throw that touches the top shelf and stops on the bin.
single_game_results.overall: The ball will likely go inside of the bin based on the scale in images. This is near impossible again. Seems AI generated, boring and near impossible to achieve. Ball inside of bin? Maybe. On bin? Makes no sense.

This is another near impossible game to do. The AI does not understand the physics it seems or nuances of instructions, and games whether or not they are even probable in some cases possible. Nonsense, boring game. Not interested.
single_game_results.explain: Place the bin near the rug and make sure it stays there. Hold and throw a dodgeball so it lands and remains on top of the hexagonal bin. 1 point for each time you make it and it rests on top of the bin.

single_game_results.overall: This game is near impossible. There is no point in scoring points for placing an object on the floor. This is not human at all, boring and nonsense. The game is near unachievable. Just not good.
single_game_results.explain: Pick up an dput down green triangle blocks. Throw dodgeballs onto the desk and basketballs onto a hexagonal bin. 1 point for each time you pick up and put down a triangle block, 1 point for each ball that stops on the desk (dodgeball) and for each that stops on the hex bin (basketball)>

single_game_results.overall: This just makes no sense at all what so ever to be a game. It is silly. You are just moving objects nonsensically without being able to repeat anything to generate points or competition even with yourself.
single_game_results.explain: Put the bin near the rug, make sure it stays. Move the chairs into the desks in the room and place teddy bears on the desks without them being diagonal. 80 points given for each chair on a desk and 1 point for each teddy bear on a desk not positioned diagonally.
Throw dodgeballs into the hex bin. 1 point given for each dodgeball that stops moving inside the bin, and makes it into the bin (assumed)
single_game_results.overall: This is just sort of basketball using dodgeballs and a hex bin. One point per good throw made in and stopping movement. Movement should not matter eventually all in the bin stop moving. This is silly AI generated talk. It is a game, just boring normal average.

single_game_results.explain: Put a hex bin by the rug keep it there for the game. Place chairs on desks in the room, throw golfballs onto desks throw dodgeballs into the bin and stack cube blocks on top of each other. 1 point for each chair on the desk, 1 for a golfball stopping on a desk, 1 for a dodgeball that stops inside and on top of the hex bin, one point for each 3 cube stack where one is on top of another and the third block is the same type on top of the first two.
single_game_results.overall: Nonsense. A ball can't stop inside and then on top of a bin. Stacking cubes for points? There are limited cubes, not a game at all. Throwing golf balls onto desks watching them or trying to get them to stop? Impossible to play with these rules. Just, boring and nonsense.

debrief_responses.strategy: I went with are they able to actually be played, is it possible within the realm of physics and then is it fun or not. That was the strategy. As if I was playing or instructed.
debrief_responses.aids: None at all. Just my mind, common sense, logic and what I consider fun or games.
debrief_responses.techDifficulties: None at all, went quite well.
debrief_responses.comments: Pretty interesting task, AI is close to but not quite ready to design games for humans. Enjoyed the survey, hope you have a great day!

debrief_responses.strategy: I thought back to when I was a child, and the sorts of games I would play. Even though I was a child, the games I would play with the other kids were far more intricate than the games that were described.

single_game_results.explain: You will throw cube blocks, a credit card, and CDs into a bin. You get points for the latter 2, but lose points for the blocks.
single_game_results.overall: If the blocks take away points, why would you choose to throw them in the bin in the first place?
It's badly designed because every ball would stop moving inside the bin. There's no real chance.
single_game_results.explain: You must throw balls into the bin, you gain 10 points after you're done throwing balls.
It's simplified skeeball you can play at home.
single_game_results.overall: It's just simplified skeeball you can play at home, instead of at an arcade.

single_game_results.explain: You must throw balls and make them land on the rim of the bin without falling.
single_game_results.overall: Physics would make it extremely difficult to play this game.

single_game_results.explain: You try and have dodgeballs land on the rim of the bin, and also you redecorate your room.
single_game_results.overall: Having balls land and stay on the rim of the bin is borderline impossible, and moving items around the room is far too easy.

single_game_results.explain: You throw balls on top of a rug.
single_game_results.overall: What's the point of placing the bin on top of the rug if it's not relevant to the way you obtain points?

single_game_results.explain: You throw balls and try to make them land inside the bin or the dog bed.
single_game_results.overall: It's just basketball but without you running around.
It's a very simple game, but seems fair to play.
single_game_results.explain: You try to land teddy bears on top of a pillow.
You throw balls and try to make them land on a dog bed or inside the bin.
single_game_results.overall: It's extremely simple, and also the description does not tell you where to place the dog bed or bin.
This game sounds like a recipe for broken glass.
single_game_results.explain: You throw dodge balls around the room and try to avoid them touching the dog bed.

debrief_responses.aids: No, I did not use any external aids to help with the task.
debrief_responses.techDifficulties: No, I did not have any technical difficulties while completing the experiment.
debrief_responses.strategy: I read the descriptions of the games and thought about how it would look like if I am playing it. Then, I jot it down based on the steps that I had in mind. I used the original description and paraphrased it a bit when I had difficulty of understanding on how the game should be played.

single_game_results.overall: This game is somewhat confusing to me but I think that it has the potential to be a good game.
single_game_results.explain: Essentially, there is a hexagonal bin in the game and you have to make sure that you place it near the rug and make sure that it stays there for the entire game. For the game play, you will be moving chairs on to desks and placing teddy bears on them, making sure that you are not positioning it diagonally. You will be scored based on how many chairs and teddy bears that are not positioned diagonally at the end of the game. Each chair on a desk will be worth 80 points and each teddy bear will be worth 1 point.

In this game, you stack blocks in certain ways and throw red dodgeballs. You earn points by making stacks of the balls. The point system consist of different combinations and each combination is worth certain points. Each time you throw a red dodgeball and it stops, you get a point.
single_game_results.overall: This game is far too confusing and I hate it.
I think I played this type of game before and it is a decent game.
single_game_results.explain: In this game you just throw dodgeballs and hope they land in the bin. If the dodgeball stops moving inside the bin, you get a point.

single_game_results.overall: I think that this game is simple. I played this type of game before so it was easy to understand. Overall, it is a decent game.
single_game_results.explain: In this game you just throw dodgeballs in a hexagonal bin. For each dodgeball that you throw in the bin and stops moving, you get 1 point.

single_game_results.overall: This game is very understandable and simple. It could be very fun to play.
single_game_results.explain: In this game, you have to throw dodgeballs to the top of the shelf. The balls have to stay still on the top shelf. You have 30 seconds to throw balls. You will earn a point for each dodgeball that is still on the top shelf at the end of the game.

single_game_results.overall: This game seems to be a good game but I think you can get bored from it after playing for a while. Overall it is not really creative because I think that anyone can come up with it.
single_game_results.explain: In this game, there will be a hexagonal bin under the rug that will remain there for the entire game. To play the game, you have to throw a dodgeball so that it touches the top shelf and have to land and rest on the hexagonal bin. You will earn a point if the ball you threw touches the top shelf and ends up on the hexagonal bin.

In this game, there will be a dodgeball near the desk. You have to throw the dodgeball so that it touches the south wall while it is still moving and you have to make sure that the dodgeball or teddy bear is not in your hand when it's in motion. The game will last for 60 seconds. You will earn a point every time you successfully throw the dodgeball and it touches the south wall and stops moving.
single_game_results.overall: I do not like this game. I think that I would get pretty frustrated playing this game.

single_game_results.explain: For this game you will need a curved wooden ramp next to the rug and make sure that it stays there throughout the game. To play the game you will need a beach ball and throw it in a way so that it will roll on the curved wooden ramp and stops on the rug. You will earn points based on where the beachball stops.
single_game_results.overall: I think that this game is interesting and well thought out. It should be fun to play.
Its a boring game. I don't think that I would like to play it.
single_game_results.explain: To setup this game, you need to have all the blocks on the rug and make sure that they don't move throughout the game. You will then throw the cube blocks and you will be scored based on the number of different cube blocks you threw which will make up your total score at the end of the game.
In this game, you will be throwing a ball at a wall and need to catch it when it bounces. You will get a point if you catch the ball after it bounces off the wall.
single_game_results.overall: This game is too easy to play. I think that the ball will always land in your hands if you throw it at a wall.

debrief_responses.comments: Maybe use different pictures for each game, as far as I can remember, the same 4 pictures were used for all of the different games, which didn't really help me imagine myself playing.
debrief_responses.strategy: I considered myself playing the game in an actual virtual environment, so not like I was playing the game in real life, however the games seemed like they would be more fun or interesting if they were played in real life and not a virtual environment. I considered the difficulty in playing a game like that, having played many many similar games both virtually and in real life, the objectives all seemed either very arbitrary or boring, and the rules weren't described well, so I just had to imagine a "perfect" game environment where I could actually attempt to play the game, and overall, the games didn't seem fun at all.

single_game_results.explain: The objective of the game is to throw dodgeballs while avoiding throwing any dodgeballs inside of the doggie bed. For every dodgeball that is thrown that successfully avoid the doggie bed, the player will get 1 point, however every dodgeball that lands inside of the doggie bed loses the player 3 points.
single_game_results.overall: The game seems very uninteresting and almost dumb, there are no rules about what direction the ball can be thrown, how the ball must be thrown, and with a small doggie bed being the only target to avoid, it would seem like the simplest way to win the game would be to just lightly toss the ball in the opposite direction to the doggie bed. On top of this, there is no terminal to the game, so the player would just continue throwing balls for no reason until they get bored (which would probably be quick).

single_game_results.explain: The objective of this game is to toss balls into a hexagonal bin. You get 15 attempts to throw the ball inside of the bin, and win if you score 6 or more points.
single_game_results.overall: This game just seems like any of the million games that exist to put a ball inside of a goal. The rules don't specify what distance the player must be from the bin so I'd imagine I could just stand right above the bin and toss them directly in. Also, the numbers of 6 makes in 15 attempts seem pretty arbitrary.

This game seems pretty ridiculous. The point of the game is to throw a ball, and you get points when the ball stops. One would assume that all balls that are thrown eventually stop, so the object of the game isn't even to make sure the balls stop moving, it is to simply throw a ball. I don't see any redeeming or appealing qualities about this game, other than potentially finding the act of throwing a ball fun.
single_game_results.explain: To play this game, you need to place a dodgeball near a desk, then pick up the dodgeball and throw it. Points are scored anytime the dodgeball is thrown and then comes to a stop.

This game seems similar to bowling or golf, in that the objective is to roll a ball and have it land on a hexagonal bin. Once a ball is thrown, the player earns 1 point, however if the dodgeball lands or stops on the bin, the player earns an additional 5 points.
single_game_results.overall: This game doesn't seem very fun. Your objective is to roll a ball near a bin. That's it. I guess it could be interesting to see if you can roll the ball in different ways, or try to get the ball on a certain side of the bin, but as it stands, the game seems very boring.

The game seems very complicated, with various ways of scoring points, however the difference in points for throwing a golfball on the bin as opposed to the other targets that award 40 points seems like a very simple strategy would quickly be made to achieve the easiest shot for the most amount of points.
single_game_results.explain: The goal of the game is to throw three different types of balls onto specific targets. Each time a golfball is thrown on a hexagonal bin, the player gets 1 point, each time a basketball is thrown on top of the top drawer, the player gets 40 points, and each time a player simultaneously throws a white golfball on top of the top drawer, a basketball on the hexagonal bin and a dodgeball on a hexagonal bin, the player scores 40 points.
After placing a hexagonal bin in the center of the room, the player must move different objects into the bin, and earn 1 point for each unique object that is successfully placed in the bin.
single_game_results.overall: This just seems like a baby game to get them to clean up their toys, just place every object you see inside of the bin and hope most of them are unique. Maybe the game could be improved if the player is penalized for every duplicate object that is put into the bin.

single_game_results.explain: After positioning a curved ramp near the center of the room facing the bed, the objective is to roll the ball over the ramp and then land on the bed in order to earn points, however if the ball doesn't land on the bed and instead comes to a stop and touches the player, the player loses points. The final score is determined by subtracting the number of times the dodgeball successfully landed on the bed by the number of times the ball missed the bed and touched the player
single_game_results.overall: I guess the game seems interesting, you want to roll the ball over the ramp at a certain speed or strength so that it lands on the bed and doesn't overshoot, however I'm confused about the ball stopping and touching the player, is the ball gravitated towards the player so that it always comes back and touches them if they miss the bed?

The game doesn't make too much sense, and maybe the description is just throwing me off, but what's the point of the green bridge blocks? And what is considered the same "type" of block? It seems like the objective of the game is to just stack blocks on top of one another, seems pretty uninteresting.
single_game_results.explain: The objective of the game is to stack different types of blocks, earning 6 points for each stack at the end of the game. The player must stack a cube shaped block and a flat block on top of a black that is the same type as the cube block.

After placing a hexagonal bin near the rug and stacking the chairs on the desks, the player must throw basketball so that they land on top of the hexagonal bin. The player earns 1 point for every chair that is stacked on a desk, and 40 points for every basketball that lands on top of the bin.
single_game_results.overall: So the game is like two different games, each with their own scoring systems. Stacking chairs on tables seems like it would be a waste of time considering you only get 1 point, while it might obstruct the vision or movement of the ball, which gains 40 points when it lands on the bin. Seems like the game should just be throwing a basketball in the bin, no chairs involved.
This game seems pretty boring and simple. Just throw a dodgeball on top of the bin. My overall impression here is pretty negative simply because it seems so mundane.
single_game_results.explain: This game is very simple, throw a dodgeball on top of a hexagonal bin. The player earns 1 point for each dodgeball that successfully lands on top of the bin.

single_game_results.overall: It seems like it would be a fun game to play. However there isn't much involved with it and it seems like a game that young children would make up and play when they don't have anything better to do.
single_game_results.explain: You will put the balls on the bed in this game.  By the end of the game, each different ball placed on the bed gives you 1 point.

single_game_results.overall: This game seems very confusing to me. I don't quite understand how the scoring works or what the point of it is.
single_game_results.explain: The goal of the game is to move objects to be near the rug and the door as well as breaking them. For the scoring for this game your score is 0.7 times the amount of objects near the door as well as the rug and the number of broken objects.

Place and keep a hexagonal bin next to the bed without any teddy bears or pillows on the bed during the game. The goal is to stand next to the desk and try to throw the balls inside the hexagonal bin. You earn 10 points for each dodgeball, 20 for each basketball, and 30 for each beachball. You lose 1 point for each ball that misses the bin.
single_game_results.overall: This game seems rather fun to me. I played some that were similar but not quite the same as this one when I was younger. The scoring system and way the game is played makes a lot of sense to me and makes the game enjoyable to play or watch.

The game seems quite fun to play and a bit of a higher skill to keep the dodgeball on the bin. I think it would be just as enjoyable to watch as it would be to play. The scoring system also seems fair to me which makes the game overall a good one in my opinion.
single_game_results.explain: The point of this game is to throw a dodgeball so that it lands and stays on a hexagonal bin. You score 1 point for each time you successfully have the dodgeball stay on the bin.

single_game_results.overall: The game seems very similar to basketball and is always an enjoyable one to play. It is fairly simple to setup and shouldn't cause too much of a mess. I think it would be as enjoyable to watch as it would be to play.
single_game_results.explain: For this game you want to place the hexagonal bin near the north wall of the room and keep it there for the whole game. The goal is to throw basketballs and dodgeballs into the bin. You score 1 point per dodgeball you get in the bin and 0.1 for each basketball.

This game is about stacking the different blocks in a specific order, doing so properly gives you 10 points for each different set of blocks you successfully stack in the right order. The order that the blocks need to be placed in are a flat block on a bridge block first. Followed by a tall cylindrical block on the black, then a cube block on the tall cylindrical block, with a pyramid block on the top of the cube block.
single_game_results.overall: This game seems like a very fun game to watch and play. The scoring system seems very fair to me. Stacking blocks is always a good idea for a simple game and it has no chance for much of a mess to clean up afterwards. I would definitely want to try this game.

single_game_results.explain: Start off by placing a hexagonal bin near the door and keep it there for the whole game. The goal of the game is to put credit cards or CDs into the bin as well as throwing white golfballs into it and having them come to a stop. You get 40 points for each credit card or CD you place in the bin and 1 point for each white golfball you throw into the bin that comes to a stop.
single_game_results.overall: This game is very confusing to me. I don't completely understand the point of it or how it is supposed to be fun to play or watch. I wouldn't really want to try this one or recommend it.

single_game_results.explain: This game you want to throw dodgeballs so they land inside and on top of the hexagonal bin. You will score 1 point for each dodgeball that stops moving when it is inside and on top of the bin.
single_game_results.overall: This game doesn't make a whole lot of sense to me. I'm confused about what the point of it is and how you actually play it. I don't think it is physically possible for the dodgeball to be both inside and on top of the bin at once.

single_game_results.explain: In this game you will place the hexagonal bin near the rug and keep it there the whole game. The point is to throw dodgeballs and tan cylindrical blocks at the bin and have the dodgeballs land on top of the bin but the tan cylindrical blocks land inside. You score 1 point for each dodgeball that lands on top of the bin and 6 points for each additional one that lands on top. Then 1 point for each tan cylindrical block that lands inside the bin, with your final score being the sum of all the points earned.
single_game_results.overall: The scoring for this game doesn't make the most sense to me. It also doesn't sound the most enjoyable but I may not understand it fully. I would try it and see if my impression changes but it just seems a bit too complicated to me.

This game has some good aspects to it and seems like it would be fun to play. I don't necessarily like the scoring system for it but I would want to try it anyway and wouldn't mind watching others play it either.
single_game_results.explain: In this game you will want to stack three blocks on top of a rectangular block but two of the stacked blocks have to be the same type as the tall rectangular block. The score that you earn is 1.4 multiplied by the number of correct stacks that you finish with.

debrief_responses.comments: Thank you for the opportunity to take part in this research.
debrief_responses.strategy: I mostly evaluated the games based on familiarity to games that I've played before or if they would be enjoyable to watch or play. The games had to make sense to me as well and I used my experience to help me judge which ones I would enjoy.
